                        "ProjectNote": {
                            "val": "This is a New program beginning in FY2020."
                        },
                        "ProjectMissionDescription": {
                            "val": "This Program Element (PE) funds hypersonic development efforts performed by the US Army Space and Missile Defense Command\/Army Forces Strategic Command (USASMDC\/ARSTRAT).\n\nProject HX1: Funds USASMDC\/ARSTRAT to prototype a Long Range Hypersonic Weapon (LRHW) System is to provide the Army with a prototype strategic attack weapon system to defeat Anti Access\/Area Denial (A2\/AD) capabilities, suppress adversary Long Range Fires, and engage other high payoff\/time sensitive targets.  The LRHW Integrated System contractor will integrate Common Hypersonic Glide Bodies (CHGBs) with 2 stage boosters into canisters to create LRHW All Up Rounds (AUR) as detailed in the following sections and a build a prototype LRHW System. A leave behind prototype LRHW system is expected as an Early Operational Capability (EOC)."
                        },
